{{Infobox person | name = Beverly Camhe | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = ]]'' | birth_place = [[Boston]] | other_names = | residence = [[New York City]] | alma_mater = [[Boston University]] & [[New York University]] | nationality = American | occupation = Producer | title = Producer | boards = | website = | signature . = | death . = | spouse = | children = 2 | years active = }} '''Beverly Camhe''' is an American producer for theater and film. She is best known for producing ''[[Junior (1994 film)|Junior]]'' in 1994 with [[Universal Studios]], directed by [[Ivan Reitman]] and starring [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]], [[Danny De Vito]] and [[Emma Thompson]] and ''[[The Package (1989 film)|The Package]]'' with [[Gene Hackman]] and [[Tommy Lee Jones]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0131771/|title=Beverly J. Camhe|website=IMDb}}</ref>
==Education== Camhe completed her Bachelor's in Philosophy from [[Boston University]]. She went on to complete the PhD Program in Cinema Studies at [[New York University]].
==Career== Camhe formed her own production company in 1985 called Beverly Camhe Productions. The company’s first production was the highly rated movie of the week ''Obsessed with a Married Woman'' starring Jane Seymore. With [[Orion Pictures]], Camhe then produced ''The Believers'' in 1987, directed by John Schlesinger and starring [[Martin Sheen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rogerebert.com/cast-and-crew/beverly-camhe|title=Beverly Camhe Movie Reviews & Film Summaries - Roger Ebert|website=www.rogerebert.com}}</ref> She also produced ''[[The Package (1989 film)|The Package]]'' in 1989, directed by Andrew Davis and starring Gene Hackman and [[Tommy Lee Jones]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1988-12-18/entertainment/ca-604_1_executive-producer|title=Films now going into production:|first=Compiled by David|last=Pecchia|date=18 December 1988|publisher=|via=LA Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://catalog.afi.com/Catalog/PersonDetails/256112|title=AFI-Catalog|website=catalog.afi.com}}</ref>
With [[Universal Studios]], Camhe produced the comedy hit, ''[[Junior (1994 film)|Junior]]'' in 1994, directed by [[Ivan Reitman]] and starring [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]], [[Danny De Vito]] and [[Emma Thompson]]. Camhe developed ''The Jimmy Roselli Story'' as a vehicle for John Travolta (1999) to be directed by [[Gus Van Sant]] but it never went into production.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/person/791027%7C0/Beverly-Camhe/filmography.html|title=Filmography for Beverly Camhe|website=Turner Classic Movies}}</ref>
Camhe produced ''[[The Celestine Prophecy (film)|The Celestine Prophecy]]'' in 2006 based on the best selling, transformational novel by [[James Redfield]], and documentary on the [[Bernard Madoff]] financial crime of the century, ''In God We Trust'', in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/god-we-trust-tribeca-review-443402|title=In God We Trust: Tribeca Review|publisher=}}</ref> Camhe then produced ''Tiny Tears'' in 2014; the documentary deals with the AIDS crisis of orphaned children in Thailand.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.adweek.com/digital/michaels-restaurant-celebrities-55/|title=Harvey Weinstein Leads the Movie Mogul Charge|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/phoenix/article/ILLUMINATES-Take-Twenty-Mentoring-Sessions-Shines-20180509|title=ILLUMINATE'S Take Twenty Mentoring Sessions Shines|first=BWW News|last=Desk|publisher=}}</ref>
==Personal== Camhe lives in the [[New York City]] area.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/06/05/nyregion/05century.html|title=Next to Central Park, Anger Over a Planned Bar|first=Javier C.|last=Hernández|date=4 June 2010|publisher=|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbiz411.com/2010/12/11/elaine-kaufman-gets-an-a-list-send-off-from-friends|title=Elaine Kaufman Gets An A List Send Off from Friends|date=11 December 2010|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hamptons.com/Out-And-About/Within-The-Hedges/17424/Art-Southampton-Kickoff-Party-Draws-Hundreds-Of.html#.WxncG1ZKhAY|title=Art Southampton Kickoff Party Draws Hundreds Of Hamptons Art Lovers - Out And About - Within The Hedges|website=www.hamptons.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/2005/04/05/jane-fonda-dishes-on-ted-turner-in-book.html|title=Jane Fonda Dishes on Ted Turner in Book|first=Roger|last=Friedman|date=5 April 2005|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/people/news/Beverly-Camhe/|title=Beverly Camhe News|website=www.broadwayworld.com}}</ref>
