{{Infobox religious building | building_name = Roknolmolk Mosque | infobox_width = | image = | caption = | map_type = Iran | map_size = 275 | location = [[Takht-e Foulad]], [[Isfahan]], [[Iran]] | coordinates = {{coord|32.628333|51.685556|display=inline,title}} | religious_affiliation = [[Shia Islam]] | rite = | region = | state = | province = [[Isfahan Province|Isfahan]] | territory = | prefecture = | sector = | district = | cercle = | municipality = [[Isfahan]] | consecration_year = | status = | functional_status = | heritage_designation = | leadership = | website = | architecture = yes | architect = | architecture_type = [[Mosque]] | architecture_style = [[Isfahani style|Isfahani]] | general_contractor = | facade_direction = | groundbreaking = | year_completed = | construction_cost = | specifications = | capacity = | length = | width = | width_nave = | height_max = | dome_quantity = | dome_height_outer = | dome_height_inner = | dome_dia_outer = | dome_dia_inner = | minaret_quantity = | minaret_height = | spire_quantity = | spire_height = | materials = | nrhp = | added = | refnum = | designated = }} '''Roknolmolk Mosque''' ({{lang-fa|مسجد رکن الملک}}) is a historical [[mosque]] in [[Isfahan]]. This mosque has been built in [[Qajar dynasty|Qajar]] era and is close to [[Takht-e Foulad]]. It was built by [[Roknolmolk|Mirza Soleyman Khan Shirazi "Roknolmolk"]], who was a prominent personage in Isfahan. The [[Portal (architecture)|Portal]] of the mosque has been decorated with the Roknolmolk's [[painting]]s and [[poem]]s.<ref>{{cite book|title=Rāhnamā ye Safar be Ostān e Esfāhān(Travel Guide for the Province Isfahan)|publisher=Rouzane|isbn=964-334-218-2|author=Hosseyn Yaghoubi|editor=Arash Beheshti|page=107|language=Persian|year=2004}}</ref>
